The place, the people and the vibes.

tip.text: Well needed place in the north, better-than-usual selection of stores
Just love the vibes of this place. RS cars are on the 4th level.
Nothing quite like going to this place - on a secluded hill, plenty of parking spaces, good food and great tea
Nice service centre with refreshments while you wait for your car. Queues are rather Long on some days though.
They occasionally have nice flowers here, but they're not as consistent as Far East flora. Also, their cold room doesn't have nearly as many flowers.
This place used to be really private and full of good feels. Lack of advancement and the fact that they open the canteen to the public who have no membership whatsoever really soiled the exclusivity.
Seafood Aglio Olio is really good for the price, I would say the portion is a little small but for a cafe it really hits above the bar. Jap curry rice was nice too.
Not many places in SG where you can see the entire city skyline, but this is one of them. Great spot to chill at night, or do a little stargazing on the grass patch when the sky is clearer.
Strong recommend for this place. Authentic and affordable, free flow bean sprout and 80% done eggs. Don't go for thick soup, it's really really thick. Go for hard noodles.
Signature charcoal waffle tastes interesting, definitely a must try. Their earl grey lavender ice cream is thick and smooth, a little heavy but pretty nice

tip.text: On an overall, the food is surprisingly good for a cafe. Place is pretty nice and prices are affordable. Signature wings are a must try!
Vibrant yet cosy place..would be a lot nicer if their food quality matched their drinks. Dishes were either underwhelming or extremely heavy in taste. Beers are not cold but acceptable
Huge burgers, would have enjoyed a slightly smaller burger with a slightly smaller hole in my pocket.. Meats taste great but the free flow fries were way overfried
Love, love, LOVE the pork knuckles. Sauerkraut and potato cubes are great too. Paulaner on tap!

Feeding the Deers, make sure you buy the biscuits for maximum fun with them
Mediocre food. Beef soup tastes like it was made from cabbages
Green tea latte is good. Avoid the wagyu burger, it's soft through and through. Ragout beef was too tough on some pieces and too soft on others. Hipster vibes all over, it wasn't worth it. $60
The Lawry's rib is soooo good. Tender on the inside yet firm on the outside for the medium rare, it goes very well with the house sauce. Wine goes with meat very well too!
Scallop porridge. Siew Mai and har gao were overcook but still pretty okay. Overall a nice supper spot but on the costly side
